{{Infobox language |name=Abu' |nativename=Ua |states=[[Papua New Guinea]] |region=[[East Sepik Province]] |speakers={{sigfig|2,555<!--original figure-->|2}} |date=2000 census |ref=e18 |familycolor=Papuan |fam1=[[Torricelli languages|Torricelli]] |fam2=[[Arapesh languages|Arapesh]] |iso3=aah |glotto=abua1245 |glottorefname=Abu' Arapesh }}
'''Abu’''', also known as '''Ua''' (meaning 'no'), is an [[Arapesh language]] ([[Torricelli languages|Torricelli]]) of [[Papua New Guinea]]. Speakers are shifting to [[Tok Pisin]].
