{{Infobox language |name=Hagahai |nativename=Pinai |states=Papua New Guinea |region=[[Enga Province|Enga]]–[[Madang Province|Madang]] border |speakers=600 |date=1997 |ref=e18 |familycolor=Papuan |fam1=[[Piawi languages|Piawi]] |iso3=pnn |glotto=pina1252 |glottorefname=Pinai-Hagahai }} '''Hagahai''', also known as '''Pinai''', is one of two languages of the [[Piawi languages|Piawi family]] of New Guinea.
Speakers in Enga Province use the name ''Pinai'' for all Pinai-Hagahai speakers. Those in Madang use Hagahai, at least for themselves. Exonyms include ''Wapi'' and ''Miamia'' in [[Enga language|Enga]] and ''Aramo'' in [[Haruai language|Haruai]].
Dialects are divergent, but speakers have a common identity.
