'''Shi''', or '''Nyabungu''', is a [[Bantu language]] of the [[Democratic Republic of the Congo]].
The Nyindu variety is heavily influenced by [[Lega language|Lega]], and speakers consider it a dialect of Lega rather than Shi, as Shi speakers see it. Maho (2009) leaves it unclassified as JD.501.<ref name="Guthrie"/>
