'''Syntaxis''' is a style in writing or in [[rhetoric]] that favors complex [[syntax]], in contrast to the simple [[sentence (linguistics)|sentence]] structures of [[parataxis]]. For example, 19th-century [[German language|German]] academic [[prose]], and [[John Milton]]'s "[[Paradise Lost]]" poetry in [[English language|English]] are notably syntactic.  Syntaxis may – depending on the author – also contrast with, or include, [[hypotaxis]].

